                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d848">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12643.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Governor Carranza leaves tomorrow for Saltillo. He will not name representatives
                    to confer with the representatives of Carbajal. He will treat with them
                    personally. He is disposed to try his utmost to arrange for a prompt, amicable
                    transfer of government and for the surrender of the army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
